---
export const prerender = true;

import { site } from '../data/site';
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout title={`${site.name} | About`} description="Learn what MACROS is building and how the app is designed to work.">
	<section class="page-header">
		<div class="container">
			<h1>Designed for simple, accurate daily tracking.</h1>
			<p>
				MACROS is an iPhone-first calorie and macro tracker built around
				clear daily totals, flexible input methods, and local-first behavior.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container detail-grid">
			<article class="detail-card">
				<h2>Why it exists</h2>
				<p>
					Tracking should feel fast and trustworthy. The app is focused on removing
					friction without forcing sign-up or hiding the numbers that matter.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="detail-card">
				<h2>Core inputs</h2>
				<p>
					Barcode scan, nutrition label photo, and manual entry are all part of the
					main workflow so logging still works when one path fails.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article class="detail-card">
				<h2>What you review</h2>
				<p>
					Each entry is built to surface serving size, quantity, calories, protein,
					carbs, and fat before it becomes part of your day.
				</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="container page-panel">
			<h2>Product direction</h2>
			<ul class="support-list">
				<li>No required login to start tracking.</li>
				<li>Local-first storage for day-to-day use.</li>
				<li>Editable nutrition data when source information is incomplete.</li>
				<li>Daily summaries derived from what you actually logged.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>
